CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 18 reads: "7. in Brotherhood Memorial Park booth were representatives William Barnett, the Rev. W.D. Petett, Charles Davis and Max Frishman. Mrs. Beulah Staples of 2323 Reed St., was presented a deed to a family plot in Brotherhood Memorial park as a grand prize"
TitMainTitle: William Barnett, Rev. W.D. Petett, Charles Davis, and Max Frishman standing in Brotherhood Memorial Park booth in Syria Mosque for the 1957 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
